                        <condition key="other">
                           <p>Deficient. The manuscript shows traces of extensive use. Many folios are worn and discoloured, the text abraded, rubricated lined poorly visible (esp. fols. <locus target="#1 #22"/>etc.). Many folios bear water stains. The sewing is repaired with threads of various types. Fol. <locus target="#21"/>of a different size, might have been inserted later to substitute for the folio which was lost. Fols. <locus target="#21"/>and <locus target="#31"/>are held in the quires with stitches, fol. <locus target="#111"/>is held with a parchment guard. Quire XVI is reinforced with two parchment guards (one of them has some writing on the inner side). Big holes are mended on fols. <locus target="#24"/>
                              <locus from="85" to="86"/>, <locus target="#137 #145"/>. </p>
                           
                        </condition>
