                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">Second half of the 18th – first half of the 19th-century script;  careful, trained hand.<note>
                           <p>Unknown</p>
                           
                        </note>
                        <note>
                           <p>- Mistaken words are encircled with thin black lines on fols. <locus target="#5v #43r #74r #83v"/>etc.</p>
                           <p>- Erasures are on fols. <locus target="#20v #26r #38v #52v #60v #69v #97v #108r"/>probably of mistaken words</p>
                           <p>- Omissions have been inserted interlineally, fols. <locus target="#2r #3v"/>
                              <locus from="5r"/>v, <locus target="#43r #48r"/>etc.</p>
                           <p>- In order to accommodate longer text lines, the scribe employed compressed script, fols. <locus target="#1v #5r #6r"/>
                              <locus from="7r"/>v, <locus target="#10r #17v"/>etc., and runovers marked with red and black dots, fols. <locus target="#3v"/>
                              <locus from="6r"/>v, <locus from="7r"/>v, <locus target="#12v"/>
                              <locus from="13r"/>v, <locus target="#10v #17v #31v #33v"/>etc., or with black and/or red lines, <locus target="#31v #43v #48r #50r #40v"/>etc.</p>
                           <p>- The scribe reduced the size of his handwriting for Texts I-<locus target="#4"/>and I-<locus target="#5"/>
                           </p>
                           <p>- In the Psalms numbering, no. <locus target="#23"/>is missing, no. <locus target="#27"/>is repeated twice</p>
                           <p>- Midpoint of the Psalms is marked on fol. <locus target="#62v"/>.</p>
                        </note>
                        <seg type="rubrication">
                           Executed possibly in the main hand, yet remarkably left-sloping; the scribe used a pen with a narrow nib. 
                           
                        </seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>

                     <decoNote type="other" xml:id="d2">
                        <p>- Daily readings are indicated by the names of the days of the week written in the top margin on fols. <locus target="#1r #25v #66v #73v #79r #80r #90r #101r"/>(<locus target="#110r"/>recent, in pen), <locus target="#116r"/>(possibly the same hand as note <locus target="#5"/>see below)</p>
                        <p>- Green/red threads are inserted in the outer margin of fol. <locus target="#44"/>and white strings fols. <locus target="#58 #101 #110"/>.</p>
                        
                     </decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="mixed" xml:id="d3">
                        <p>- Polychrome ornamental band on fol. <locus target="#1r"/>
                        </p>
                        <p>- Design of the cross on fol. <locus target="#16r"/>
                        </p>
                        
                     </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
